strious physician from Pergamon, and the first complete alphabetical lexicon in Western literature. Along with the critical text edition, the volume also includes an extensive introduction, Italian translation, comments, and indexes.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Modern (1453-).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMedicine, Greek and RomanvEarly works to 1800. 4aGalen. 4aHippokrates. 4aMedizin/ Antike. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aPerilli, Lorenzo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2017z9783110547733oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104807400 cprintz978311048072640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311048196940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110481969423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110481969/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017